{"id":29344869,"date":"2026-04-30T13:09:40","date_gmt":"2026-04-30T07:39:40","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/?p=29344869"},"modified":"2026-04-30T13:20:59","modified_gmt":"2026-04-30T07:50:59","slug":"career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management","title":{"rendered":"Career After MBA in Human Resource Management (HRM): Jobs, Salaries &amp; Scope in India"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_82_2 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\" style=\"cursor:inherit\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" aria-label=\"Toggle Table of Content\"><span class=\"ez-toc-js-icon-con\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#What_is_an_MBA_in_Human_Resource_Management\" >What is an MBA in Human Resource Management?&nbsp;<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#Key_Highlights_of_MBA_in_HRM\" >Key Highlights of MBA in HRM<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#Why_Choose_an_MBA_in_Human_Resources\" >Why Choose an MBA in Human Resources?<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#Skills_Needed_for_an_MBA_in_Human_Resource_Management_Job_Roles\" >Skills Needed for an MBA in Human Resource Management Job Roles&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#MBA_in_Human_Resource_Management_Job_Roles_Salaries_in_India\" >MBA in Human Resource Management Job Roles &amp; Salaries in India<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#For_Freshers\" >For Freshers<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#For_Experienced\" >For Experienced<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#Government_Jobs_After_an_MBA_in_HR_Degree\" >Government Jobs After an MBA in HR Degree<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#Top_Recruiters_Hiring_MBAs_in_HR_in_India\" >Top Recruiters Hiring MBAs in HR in India<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#How_to_Plan_Your_Career_Path_After_an_MBA_in_HRM\" >How to Plan Your Career Path After an MBA in HRM?<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#Career_Scope_MBA_in_HRM_vs_Other_MBA_Specializations\" >Career Scope: MBA in HRM vs Other MBA Specializations&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\/#FAQs\" >FAQs&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n<p>Pursuing an MBA in Human Resource Management (HRM) can be quite helpful in learning the vital people management skills that are essential in today\u2019s competitive professional landscape. The course helps learners gain the much-desired skills to manage, motivate, and encourage organizational growth by effectively handling the organization&#8217;s most valuable asset\u2014its human resources.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This blog shares more details about the MBA in HRM degree program and the MBA HR salary, so you know what to expect before taking the course.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_is_an_MBA_in_Human_Resource_Management\"><\/span><strong>What is an MBA in Human Resource Management?&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Human Resource Management (HRM) has long been a popular choice among students in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-courses\"><strong>MBA programs<\/strong><\/a>. The program helps graduates land high-paying, rewarding roles in various organizations, particularly in senior management or leadership positions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the key specialized skills that professionals learn in MBA HRM courses are organizational behavior, strategic talent management, and talent acquisition.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Key_Highlights_of_MBA_in_HRM\"><\/span><strong>Key Highlights of MBA in HRM<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An MBA in HR is a highly popular specialization among MBA aspirants in India, as the course unlocks numerous career pathways across multiple industries and sectors for graduates. Below are the key highlights of the course:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Key Highlights<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Description<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Duration<\/td><td>2 years (24 months) \/ 4 semesters<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Job Roles<\/td><td>Talent Management Specialist, Succession Planning Manager, Performance Management Specialist<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Average MBA in HR Management Salary<\/td><td>INR 5 LPA (approx)<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Key Subjects<\/td><td>Business Communication, Performance Management and Appraisal, HR Analytics<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Top Recruiters<\/td><td>Google, Deloitte, Accenture<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Indeed<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Why_Choose_an_MBA_in_Human_Resources\"><\/span><strong>Why Choose an MBA in Human Resources?<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>HR is a high-demand MBA specialization, as the program equips learners with skills to shape workplace culture, hire, manage, and retain talent, and drive organizational success.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>The course opens numerous opportunities in diverse roles such as learning &amp; development, talent acquisition and management, and HR analytics.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>There is consistently high demand for HR professionals across various industries, with assured career growth and competitive MBA in Human Resource Management salaries proportionate to skills and experience.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The course equips learners with specialized skills, such as people management, leadership potential, and strategic decision-making.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Skills_Needed_for_an_MBA_in_Human_Resource_Management_Job_Roles\"><\/span><strong>Skills Needed for an MBA in Human Resource Management Job Roles&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The average MBA in HR salary package after course completion likely goes higher as you acquire specialized skills in the domain. Some of the essential skills that MBA HR courses equip learners with are:\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th><strong>Technical Skills\u00a0<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Tools &amp; Technologies<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Talent Acquisition<\/td><td>SAP SuccessFactors<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>HR Analytics &amp; Reporting<\/td><td>Power BI\/MS Excel<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Payroll Management<\/td><td>ADP Workforce Now<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Performance Management<\/td><td>Workday<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Employee Engagement Methodologies<\/td><td>Zoho People<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"MBA_in_Human_Resource_Management_Job_Roles_Salaries_in_India\"><\/span><strong>MBA in Human Resource Management Job Roles &amp; Salaries in India<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Graduates of MBA in HRM courses have a wide variety of roles to explore, such as Recruiter, HR Executive, and HR Generalist, depending on their area of specialization. Furthermore, starting salaries are commensurate with the industry and tend to increase proportionately to experience.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"For_Freshers\"><\/span><strong>For Freshers<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Entry-level MBA HR graduates can start in roles such as HR Assistant or HR Executive to gain hands-on experience in the industry. The average entry-level MBA HR salary in India per month for freshers is estimated in the range of INR 16,000 &#8211; INR 20,000 (approximately).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Parameters\u00a0<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Description<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><br><br>Job Roles<\/td><td>HR Executive<br>Talent Acquisition Executive<br>HR Generalist<br>Training &amp; Development Coordinator<br>Payroll &amp; HR Operations Executive<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Salary<\/td><td>INR 4 LPA (approx)<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Key Skills<\/td><td>Talent Acquisition<br>Labor Law Compliance<br>Effective Communication and Presentation Skills<br>Negotiation<br>Conflict Resolution<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Hiring Industries<\/td><td>Consulting<br>Manufacturing<br>Construction<br>Retail<br>Healthcare Management\u00a0<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Glassdoor<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"For_Experienced\"><\/span><strong>For Experienced<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Candidates with industrial experience are eligible to apply for senior management and leadership positions, and the average monthly salary for an MBA in HR is estimated at INR 22,000 &#8211; INR 30,000 (approx.).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Parameters\u00a0<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Description<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><br><br>Job Roles<\/td><td>Talent Management Specialist<br>Succession Planning Manager<br>Performance Management Specialist<br>HR Compliance Manager<br>HR Analytics Manager<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Salary&nbsp;<\/td><td>INR 8.8 LPA (approx)<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Key Skills<\/td><td>Strategic HR Planning<br>Mentoring and Leadership<br>HR Analytics and Metrics<br>Emotional Intelligence<br>Strategic Talent Acquisition\u00a0<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Hiring Industries<\/td><td>Tourism and Hospitality<br>IT<br>Media and Publishing<br>Telecommunications<br>BFSI<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Sources: Glassdoor, AmbitionBox<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Government_Jobs_After_an_MBA_in_HR_Degree\"><\/span><strong>Government Jobs After an MBA in HR Degree<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>HR professionals can pursue secure, stable career paths in several public-sector organizations, with roles focused on recruitment, workforce management, and employee relations.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th><strong>Job Roles<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Average Annual Salary (Approx)<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>HR Manager in Government Banks<\/td><td>INR 17.4 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Government HR Head&nbsp;<\/td><td>INR 12 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Personnel Officer (Government)<\/td><td>INR 5 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Administrative Officer<\/td><td>INR 4.8 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Labour Welfare Officer<\/td><td>INR 4.3 LPA<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Sources: AmbitionBox, Glassdoor, Payscale<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Top_Recruiters_Hiring_MBAs_in_HR_in_India\"><\/span><strong>Top Recruiters Hiring MBAs in HR in India<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Human Resource Management is an essential skill required across industries and organizations, and completing an MBA in the field opens up a host of lucrative job opportunities for graduates. They are in demand from some of the leading giants in the professional space, and the average MBA in HR salary for freshers is estimated at INR 5 LPA (approx.). Some of the top names hiring MBA HR professionals in India are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Accenture<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Infosys<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hindustan Unilever<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Deloitte<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wipro\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Glassdoor<\/em>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_to_Plan_Your_Career_Path_After_an_MBA_in_HRM\"><\/span><strong>How to Plan Your Career Path After an MBA in HRM?<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Finding the best and highest-paying jobs after an MBA in HR requires careful planning and aligning your interests with industry demand and your career aspirations. Here is a step-by-step plan to chart out a rewarding career path after completing an MBA in HRM:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Identify the area within HRM that you want to specialize in. It could be HR Analytics, Talent Acquisition, Learning &amp; Development, or Compensation and Benefits. Based on your interests and what you want to pursue as a career field, make a choice.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Start gaining practical experience in the specialized field and upskill via certifications. Hands-on learning coupled with certification programs is a surefire way to advance your career.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Define a roadmap for the long term. Don\u2019t just think about the near future and how to secure a rewarding job after completing the MBA in HRM. Make a long-term plan that starts with entry-level roles, builds the required hands-on skills and experience, and gradually advances to senior management positions.\u00a0\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Read more:<\/em><\/strong> Career Path After an MBA in HR<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career_Scope_MBA_in_HRM_vs_Other_MBA_Specializations\"><\/span><strong>Career Scope: MBA in HRM vs Other MBA Specializations&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A comparison of job opportunities and MBA in Human Resource Management salaries in India, using the same parameters (job + salary prospects) as other MBA specializations, can help learners make informed choices for their future career paths. The table below presents these parameters to help you learn which MBA specialization can help assure you a more promising future ahead.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th><br><strong>MBA<\/strong> <strong>Specialization<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Job Roles<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Average Salary (Approx)<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Key Skills<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Hiring Industries<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-human-resource-management\">MBA in Human Resource Management<\/a><\/td><td>HR Manager<br>Learning &amp; Development Manager<br>Employee Relations Manager<\/td><td>INR 4.8 LPA<\/td><td>Leadership Ability<br>Managerial Skills<br>Strategic HR Planning<\/td><td>Consulting<br>Hospitality<br>Healthcare\u00a0<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-finance\">MBA in Finance<\/a><\/td><td>Corporate Finance Manager<br>Financial Planner<br>Financial Analyst&nbsp;<\/td><td>INR 7 LPA<\/td><td>Advanced Excel<br>Risk Management<br>Forecasting and Budgeting<\/td><td>Banking&nbsp;<br>Insurance&nbsp;<br>Retail Estate<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-digital-marketing\">MBA in Digital Marketing<\/a><\/td><td>Digital Marketing Manager<br>Performance Marketing Manager<br>Campaign Manager<\/td><td>INR 8 LPA<\/td><td>Data Analytics<br>Performance Measurement<br>Content Management<\/td><td>E-Commerce &amp; Retail<br>EdTech<br>Healthcare<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-analytics-data-science\">MBA in Data Analytics<\/a><\/td><td>Data Analyst<br>Marketing Analyst<br>Analytics Manager<\/td><td>INR 11 LPA<\/td><td>Statistical &amp; Quantitative Skills<br>Data Visualization<br>Data Analysis &amp; Interpretation<\/td><td>E-Commerce<br>FinTech<br>Cybersecurity<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-project-management\">MBA in Project Management<\/a>\u00a0<\/td><td>Project Manager<br>Portfolio Manager<br>Agile Project Manager<\/td><td>INR 15 LPA<\/td><td>Risk Management<br>Strategic Planning<br>Agile Methodologies&nbsp;<\/td><td>Construction&nbsp;<br>Consulting&nbsp;<br>Healthcare&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-marketing\">MBA in Marketing<\/a><\/td><td>PR Manager<br>Digital Marketing Manager<br>Business Development Manager<\/td><td>INR 7 LPA<\/td><td>Consumer Behavior Analysis<br>Data-Driven Decision-Making Digital Marketing &nbsp;<\/td><td>Finance&nbsp;<br>Entertainment<br>Advertising&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-international-business\">MBA in International Business<\/a><\/td><td>International Trade Manager<br>Global Operations Manager<br>Import Manager<\/td><td>INR 11 LPA<\/td><td>Data Analysis<br>Decision-Making<br>Cross-Cultural Communication<\/td><td>Consulting&nbsp;<br>Travel and Tourism<br>E-Commerce<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-operations-management\">MBA in Operations Management<\/a><\/td><td>Operations Research Analyst<br>Distribution Manager<br>Production Manager<\/td><td>INR 6 LPA<\/td><td>Analytical Decision-Making&nbsp;Strategic Thinking<br>Financial Acumen&nbsp;<\/td><td>Transportation<br>&nbsp;Automotive<br>Manufacturing&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-supply-chain-management\">MBA in Supply Chain Management<\/a><\/td><td>Supply Chain Manager<br>Warehouse Manager<br>Supply Chain Analyst<\/td><td>INR 8 LPA<\/td><td>Data Visualization<br>Demand Planning<br>Inventory Management<\/td><td>Retail&nbsp;Manufacturing&nbsp;<br>E-Commerce<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-banking-financial-services-insurance\">MBA in BFSI<\/a>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Corporate Banking Manager<br>Wealth Manager<br>Insurance Manager<\/td><td>INR 8.1 LPA<\/td><td>Financial Modeling<br>Regulatory Compliance<br>Time Management<\/td><td>Corporate Finance<br>Insurance<br>Banking&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-it-fintech\">MBA in IT &amp; FinTech<\/a><\/td><td>IT Manager<br>Cybersecurity Analyst<br>IT Risk Manager<\/td><td>INR 7.7 LPA<\/td><td>AI\/ML<br>Risk Management<br>Strategic Thinking<\/td><td>Banking<br>Cybsercecurity&nbsp;<br>Consulting&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-information-system-management\">MBA in Information System Management<\/a><\/td><td>IT Project Manager<br>IT Strategist<br>Business Systems Analyst<\/td><td>INR 5.7 LPA<\/td><td>Systems Design and Analysis<br>Business Process Optimization<br>Critical Thinking<\/td><td>Automotive&nbsp;<br>Education&nbsp;Finance&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/online-mba-retail-management\">MBA in Retail Management<\/a><\/td><td>Retail Manager<br>Merchandise Planner<br>E-Commerce Manager<\/td><td>INR 7.3 LPA<\/td><td>Consumer Behavior Analysis<br>Data-Based Decision-Making<br>Inventory Management&nbsp;<\/td><td>E-Commerce<br>FMCG<br>Fashion &amp; Apparel<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Sources: Indeed, AmbitionBox, Glassdoor<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Useful Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/most-in-demand-mba-specializations\">Top 6 In-Demand MBA Specializations in 2026<\/a><\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FAQs\"><\/span><strong>FAQs&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. What is the scope of an MBA in HR Management?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>An MBA in HR Management opens up career opportunities for graduates across various industries. Students are prepared to perform everyday HR functions, such as talent acquisition, management, and retention, with greater efficiency.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Is an MBA in HR worth it?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, absolutely. An MBA in HR is totally worth it if pursued at a reputable and recognized university. The course also offers a high salary package to graduates upon completion of the program.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. What is the salary of an HR in an MBA?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>This may vary from one professional to another; however, the average salary of an MBA HR graduate in India is estimated at INR 5 LPA (approximately).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. What is the qualification for an MBA in HR?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>To pursue an MBA degree in HR, you must first obtain a three-year recognized Bachelor\u2019s degree from a recognized university or institution with a minimum of 50% aggregate at the undergraduate level. Most universities generally prefer prior work experience.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. Which HR is highly paid?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"5\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The role of a Chief Human Resources Officer (CHRO) is considered high-paying in the industry, followed by other specialized roles like VP of HR, HRIS Managers, Diversity Managers, and Compensation\/Benefits Managers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>6. How many years is an MBA in HR?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"6\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The typical duration of the program is around 2 years. However, some institutions may have a different course duration depending on the course structure and curriculum.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>7. Is an MBA in HR a stressful job?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"7\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, an MBA in HR is considered a high-pressure role, as it involves people management and conflict resolution, among other vital functions that ensure an organization&#8217;s overall success.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>8. What are the 4 types of HR?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"8\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The four major functions of HR in any organization are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Recruitment<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Training and development<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Compensation and benefits<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Employee relations<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>9. Is HR a good career after an MBA?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"9\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Absolutely! Many MBA students prefer to specialize in HR and pursue it as a career path, as there is strong demand for qualified, skilled HR professionals across industries today.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>References:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>https:\/\/in.indeed.com\/career-advice\/pay-salary\/how-much-do-mba-hr-make<br>https:\/\/glassdoor.co.in\/Salary\/Fresher-Human-Resources-Manager-India-Salaries-EJI_IE5024442.0,7_KO8,31_IL.32,37_IN115.htm<br>https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/mba-hr-salary-SRCH_KO0,6.htm<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/hr-manager-salary<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/labour-welfare-officer-salary<br>https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salary\/Government-of-India-HR-Head-Salaries-E335550_DAO.htm?filter.jobTitleExact=HR-Head&amp;filter.payPeriod=MONTHLY<br>https:\/\/www.payscale.com\/research\/IN\/Job=Administrative_Officer\/Salary<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/personnel-officer-salary?IndustryName=government<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/salaries\/state-bank-of-india-salaries\/hr-manager<br>https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/mba-hr-salary-SRCH_KO0,6.htm<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Pursuing an MBA in Human Resource Management (HRM) can be quite helpful in learning the vital people management skills that are essential in today\u2019s competitive professional landscape. The course helps learners gain the much-desired skills to manage, motivate, and encourage organizational growth by effectively handling the organization&#8217;s most valuable asset\u2014its human resources.&nbsp; This blog shares [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":29344883,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[605],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-29344869","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-mba"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>Career After MBA in Human Resource Management (HRM): Jobs, Salaries &amp; Scope in India<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Find out what to do after an MBA in Human Resource Management, with details on top jobs, salary packages, and career growth in India\u2019s HR sector.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/29344869\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Career After MBA in Human Resource Management (HRM): Jobs, Salaries &amp; Scope in India\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Find out what to do after an MBA in Human Resource Management, with details on top jobs, salary packages, and career growth in India\u2019s HR sector.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-human-resource-management\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:publisher\" content=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/onlinemanipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:published_time\" content=\"2026-04-30T07:39:40+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2026-04-30T07:50:59+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/04\/MBA-in-Human-Resource-Management-HRM_-Course-Fees-Eligibility-Jobs-Salaries.jpg\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"2400\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"794\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:type\" content=\"image\/jpeg\" \/>\n<meta name=\"author\" content=\"Ajmal V\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:label1\" content=\"Written by\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data1\" content=\"Ajmal V\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:label2\" content=\"Estim